9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 475, L.D. 733, “An Act to Make
10 Changes to the Law Based on a Pilot Project Conducted by the Maine State Housing
11 Authority Regarding Efforts to Improve Access to Credit for Low-income Renters”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'Resolve, to Require the Maine State Housing Authority to Submit a Report on the
14 Pilot Project to Improve Access to Credit for Low-income Individuals'
15 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the title and inserting the following:
16 'Sec. 1. Report. Resolved: That, by June 30, 2026, the Maine State Housing
17 Authority shall submit a report to the Joint Standing Committee on Housing and Economic
18 Development with details on the authority's pilot project to facilitate rent payment history
19 reporting to credit reporting agencies for purposes of establishing or improving the credit
20 ratings of low-income residential tenants through voluntary participation of residential
21 landlords and tenants in the State in submitting rent payment histories of tenants. The report
22 must include details on the effectiveness of collecting and reporting rent payment histories,
23 an analysis of any improvement in the credit ratings of tenant participants and
24 recommended legislation to make the pilot project permanent. The joint standing
25 committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over housing and economic development
26 matters may report out legislation based upon the report to the 133rd Legislature in 2027.'
27 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
28 number to read consecutively.
29 SUMMARY
3300 This amendment replaces the bill, which is a concept draft, with a resolve. It requires
3311 the Maine State Housing Authority to submit a report to the Joint Standing Committee on
3322 Housing and Economic Development, by June 30, 2026, about its pilot project to collect
3333 and report tenant rent payment histories to appropriate credit reporting agencies with the
3344 purpose of improving the credit ratings of low-income residential tenants. The joint
3355 standing committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over housing and economic
